A new study by British researchers reveals that women's health is much more at risk from sleep deprivation than men's.
There are two possible explanations for these results.
Is there a correlation between lack of sleep and weight gain?
The study found that a sleep deficit built up over just five nights can significantly impair heart function.
In the report, published in the Aug. 1 issue of the journal Sleep, researchers at Ohio State University in Columbus analyzed 18.6 million cases of sleep disorders in patients age 17 or younger.
